@startuml
title Intent Management end-to-end runtime sequence

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam maxMessageSize 90
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10

actor Consumer
participant "IC MS\nIntent Controller" as IC
participant "II MS\nIntent Intelligence" as II
participant "Optimiser" as OPT
participant "ICB MS\nIntent Callback" as ICB
participant "Change execution\nNetwork or fulfilment" as NET
participant "Observability\nPlatform" as OBS
participant "IA MS\nIntent Assurance" as IA

box "Internal event backbone" #F7F7F7
queue "t7.intent.management.events" as Kafka
end box

== Runtime intent admission ==

Consumer -> IC : POST /intentManagement/v5/intent
IC -> IC : Validate request shape, IntentSpecification id, expression IRI
IC -> IC : Persist runtime Intent projection\nAcknowledged
IC -> Kafka : publish IntentValidatedEvent
Kafka -> II : consume IntentValidatedEvent

== Semantic resolution and selected configuration ==

II -> II : Interpret expression context\nValidate targets, constraints, preferences
II -> II : Resolve KP and governed source facts
II -> OPT : POST /optimisation\nwhen optimisation-backed selection is required
OPT -> ICB : POST /intent-callback/v1/submissions\nOptimisationStatusChangeEventRequest
ICB -> ICB : Ingest callback and persist outbox
ICB -> Kafka : publish OptimisationStatusChangeEvent
Kafka -> II : consume OptimisationStatusChangeEvent

II -> II : Correlate optimiser outcome\nPackage selected configuration
II -> Kafka : publish IntentNetworkReadyEvent
Kafka -> IA : consume IntentNetworkReadyEvent

== Change execution and assurance ==

IA -> IA : Store selected apply resources\nand observer scope
NET -> ICB : POST /intent-callback/v1/submissions\napply or termination callback
ICB -> Kafka : publish IntentCallbackEvent
Kafka -> IA : consume IntentCallbackEvent

IA -> OBS : collect runtime metrics\nfor observer scope
OBS --> IA : resource metric facts

IA -> IA : Map callback state\nEvaluate observations against targets
IA -> Kafka : publish IntentAssuranceEvent
Kafka -> IC : consume IntentAssuranceEvent
IC -> IC : Project external Intent lifecycle\nand IntentReport
Consumer -> IC : GET /intent/{id}\nGET /intent/{id}/intentReport

== Degraded control-loop path ==

Kafka -> II : consume IntentAssuranceEvent\nDegraded only
II -> II : Evaluate degraded-state control-loop policy
II -> OPT : POST /optimisation\nif reselection or re-optimisation is allowed
OPT -> ICB : POST /intent-callback/v1/submissions\nOptimisationStatusChangeEventRequest
ICB -> Kafka : publish OptimisationStatusChangeEvent
Kafka -> II : consume OptimisationStatusChangeEvent
II -> Kafka : publish IntentNetworkReadyEvent\nnew selected configuration
Kafka -> IA : consume IntentNetworkReadyEvent

== Non-triggering assurance outcomes ==

note over II,IA
Only Degraded is a default II MS control-loop trigger.

Failed does not trigger II retry.
Retry after failure is triggered through the retrial endpoint
or a governed retry workflow.

Terminated and Paused do not trigger II MS control-loop action.
II MS must not resume paused network or service execution.

Normal degradation recovery does not require IC MS
to emit a new IntentValidatedEvent.
end note

@enduml
